            <title>[TEZ-2240] Fix toUpperCase/toLowerCase to use Locale.ENGLISH</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TEZ-2240</link>
                <project id="12314426" key="TEZ">Apache Tez</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;String#toLowerCase()/toUpperCase() without a locale argument can occur unexpected behavior based on the locale. It&apos;s written in Javadoc:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For instance, &quot;TITLE&quot;.toLowerCase() in a Turkish locale returns &quot;t\u0131tle&quot;, where &apos;\u0131&apos; is the LATIN SMALL LETTER DOTLESS I character&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-11602&quot; title=&quot;Fix toUpperCase/toLowerCase to use Locale.ENGLISH&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-11602&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-11602&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is an issue to address this problem at the Hadoop side.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
